; PERF: local-environment growth.
; A single straight-line function defining 10000 distinct temporaries,
; each reading the previous one. The local env gains one binding per
; instruction and every read searches it, so an association-list env
; makes this quadratic while a tree map keeps it n log n. Compare
; against loop-phi-arith.ll (same kind of instructions, constant-size
; env) to isolate the env-scaling cost.
;
; Tune: regenerate with a different N (see tests/perf/README.md).
; Result is sum 1..N = N*(N+1)/2.

